  "doc_id": "11091",
  "text": "This study supplements a previous study by [CITATION_1] , in which hydrological processes, including melt extent conditions, SMB, and surface runoff, were analyzed only for the Jakobshavn Isbrae catchment during the years 2001 to 2007. In the present study, we analyze the overall freshwater flux from land (2009 to 2013) and take into account the spatiotemporal routing and distribution of runoff draining into the entire Ilulissat Icefjord from 214 subcatchments. Runoff is then linked to quasi-continuous salinity and temperature observations, emphasizing the terrestrial runoff impact on hydrographic conditions inside the fjord and near the GrIS tidewater glacier margins.",
